snippet.textDisplay: IMO, Motorola has executed their product better.  for one, the screen when it's closed has more utility than Samsung's.  you can't nick them for having a slower processor, smaller battery, and inferior camera spec because those can be replaced with better spec without changing the overall design of the phone.  the only thing that's going for the Samsung is the "glass" screen, but that's debatable because to have good comparison on that feature one needs to hold the phones in person.
